<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="107" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="107">
<taxonomicName LSID="18557EB9-1366-5A4F-8DB8-E7918552317D" authority="Ghosh, 1922" authorityName="Ghosh" authorityYear="1922" class="Bivalvia" family="Arcidae" genus="Scaphula" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Scaphula minuta" order="Arcida" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="minuta">Scaphula minuta Ghosh, 1922</taxonomicName>
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Freshwater bivalves of the Tonle Sap basin, Cambodia (Arcidae, Mytilidae, Cyrenidae) A Scaphula minuta B Limnoperna fortunei C Sinomytilus harmandi D-G Corbicula spp. Scale bars: 10 mm, unless stated otherwise. Photographs by TH Ng (A-C) and K Macharoenboon (D-G)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.958.53865.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/441305" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="107" type="reference_group">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="107">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ghosh" authorityYear="1922" class="Bivalvia" family="Arcidae" genus="Scaphula" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Scaphula minuta" order="Arcida" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="minuta">Scaphula minuta</taxonomicName>
Ghosh, 1922: 1143-1144. Type locality: &quot;Tale Sap or inland Sea of Singgora on the east coast of peninsular Siam&quot;.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="107" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Material examined.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="107">CIFI.MOL.044, ZRC.MOL.015755.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="107" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Distribution and habitat.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Pursat River in Pursat Province, and Sreng River in Siem Reap Province (locality no. 7 and 32). Found attached to rocks in slow-moving waters.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="107" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="107">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ghosh" authorityYear="1922" class="Bivalvia" family="Arcidae" genus="Scaphula" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Scaphula minuta" order="Arcida" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="minuta">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Scaphula minuta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was first described from Songkhla Lake in southern Thailand (Ghosh 1929) and only recently reported to be distributed in southern Vietnam (
<bibRefCitation author="Bogan, AE" journalOrPublisher="Tropical Natural History" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" pagination="113 - 116" refId="B5" refString="Bogan, AE, Do, VT, 2014. Two freshwater bivalve species new to the fauna of Vietnam (Mollusca: Bivalvia: Arcidae and Unionidae). Tropical Natural History 14 (2): 113 - 116" title="Two freshwater bivalve species new to the fauna of Vietnam (Mollusca: Bivalvia: Arcidae and Unionidae)." volume="14" year="2014">Bogan and Do 2014</bibRefCitation>
). In addition, 
<bibRefCitation author="Bogan, AE" journalOrPublisher="Tropical Natural History" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" pagination="113 - 116" refId="B5" refString="Bogan, AE, Do, VT, 2014. Two freshwater bivalve species new to the fauna of Vietnam (Mollusca: Bivalvia: Arcidae and Unionidae). Tropical Natural History 14 (2): 113 - 116" title="Two freshwater bivalve species new to the fauna of Vietnam (Mollusca: Bivalvia: Arcidae and Unionidae)." volume="14" year="2014">Bogan and Do (2014)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned that past records of ' 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Benson" authorityYear="1856" class="Bivalvia" family="Arcidae" genus="Scaphula" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Scaphula pinna" order="Arcida" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="pinna">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Scaphula pinna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
' in Thailand (i.e., 
<bibRefCitation author="Brandt, RAM" journalOrPublisher="Archiv fuer Molluskenkunde" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" pagination="1 - 423" refId="B8" refString="Brandt, RAM, 1974. The non-marine aquatic Mollusca of Thailand. Archiv fuer Molluskenkunde 105: 1 - 423" title="The non-marine aquatic Mollusca of Thailand." volume="105" year="1974">Brandt 1974</bibRefCitation>
) should be referred to as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ghosh" authorityYear="1922" class="Bivalvia" family="Arcidae" genus="Scaphula" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Scaphula minuta" order="Arcida" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="minuta">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Scaphula minuta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Based on 
<bibRefCitation author="Bogan, AE" journalOrPublisher="Tropical Natural History" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" pagination="113 - 116" refId="B5" refString="Bogan, AE, Do, VT, 2014. Two freshwater bivalve species new to the fauna of Vietnam (Mollusca: Bivalvia: Arcidae and Unionidae). Tropical Natural History 14 (2): 113 - 116" title="Two freshwater bivalve species new to the fauna of Vietnam (Mollusca: Bivalvia: Arcidae and Unionidae)." volume="14" year="2014">Bogan and Do (2014)</bibRefCitation>
, the species previously identified as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Benson" authorityYear="1856" class="Bivalvia" family="Arcidae" genus="Scaphula" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Scaphula pinna" order="Arcida" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="pinna">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Scaphula pinna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and cited as being uncertain in Cambodia (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.2305/IUCN.UK.2012-1.RLTS.T171815A1332569.en" author="Madhyastha, A" journalOrPublisher="Journal de Conchyliologie" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" refId="B49" refString="Madhyastha, A, 2012. Scaphulapinna. The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species 2012: e.T171815A1332569. https://doi.org/10.2305/IUCN.UK.2012-1.RLTS.T171815A1332569.en" title="Scaphulapinna. The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species 2012: e. T 171815 A 1332569." url="https://doi.org/10.2305/IUCN.UK.2012-1.RLTS.T171815A1332569.en" year="2012">Madhyastha 2012</bibRefCitation>
) was probably 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ghosh" authorityYear="1922" class="Bivalvia" family="Arcidae" genus="Scaphula" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Scaphula minuta" order="Arcida" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="minuta">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Scaphula minuta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, the distinction between these two species is pending systematic revision, and our records represent the first confirmation of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ghosh" authorityYear="1922" class="Bivalvia" family="Arcidae" genus="Scaphula" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Scaphula minuta" order="Arcida" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="minuta">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Scaphula minuta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in Cambodia.
</paragraph>
